01:18.968 --> 01:22.467
Oh, God, the world
is ugly in the morning.

01:22.502 --> 01:23.968
Oh, Al.
It's our anniversary

01:24.003 --> 01:26.501
and the kids wanted
to fix us breakfast.

01:26.536 --> 01:28.000
Yeah, they're
great kids.

01:28.035 --> 01:30.000
By the way,
happy anniversary.

01:30.035 --> 01:33.000
Did you brush
your teeth this morning?

01:33.035 --> 01:34.501
No. You?

01:34.536 --> 01:36.400
No.

01:36.435 --> 01:37.701
Happy anniversary, honey.

01:39.267 --> 01:41.267
I could eat a horse.

01:41.302 --> 01:42.767
Me too.
I'm hungry.

01:42.802 --> 01:44.767
I don't smell
anything cooking.

01:44.802 --> 01:46.767
I don't see
anything cooking.

01:46.802 --> 01:48.868
I'm gonna go out
on a limb here-

01:48.903 --> 01:50.701
Nothing's cooking.

01:50.736 --> 01:53.300
I bet they made
something ahead of time

01:53.335 --> 01:55.100
and they're hiding.

01:55.135 --> 01:57.467
Ready to surprise us.

01:57.502 --> 01:58.801
Oh.

01:58.836 --> 02:00.968
I'm starving.
What's for breakfast?

02:01.003 --> 02:02.467
Kids!
It's our anniversary.

02:02.502 --> 02:04.901
I thought you wanted
to get up early

02:04.936 --> 02:06.000
and fix us breakfast?

02:06.035 --> 02:08.267
Oh, no.
Was that today?

02:08.301 --> 02:09.701
Uh-huh.

02:09.735 --> 02:11.400
I'm sorry.

02:11.435 --> 02:13.400
Happy anniversary.

02:13.435 --> 02:15.267
What's
for breakfast?

02:15.302 --> 02:18.267
I'll fix us something.
What would you like?

02:18.302 --> 02:21.267
I'd like some
fried eggs over easy,

02:21.302 --> 02:24.267
I'd like couple of pieces
of crisp bacon,

02:24.302 --> 02:26.767
I'd like a glass
of fresh juice, squeezed,

02:26.802 --> 02:30.267
and I'd like a couple of pieces
of toast with jam.

02:30.302 --> 02:31.667
Where's the Tang?

02:35.067 --> 02:37.734
You are so immature.

02:40.667 --> 02:42.667
Bud, stop playing
with your clothes.

02:44.467 --> 02:46.534
Well anyway,
happy anniversary, dear.

02:46.569 --> 02:49.100
Can you believe
it's been 16 years?

02:49.135 --> 02:51.467
Yeah, they just
flew by.

02:51.502 --> 02:54.801
Let's see,
now which one is the 16th?

02:54.836 --> 02:58.133
I know the 10th is tin.

02:58.168 --> 02:59.801
The 15th is crystal.

02:59.836 --> 03:01.467
What's the next one?

03:01.502 --> 03:02.634
Brimstone.

03:03.968 --> 03:06.501
Gonna get me
a tie again?

03:06.536 --> 03:07.734
Yeah.

03:07.769 --> 03:09.100
Getting me shoes?

03:09.135 --> 03:10.234
Yeah.

03:10.269 --> 03:11.567
From your store?

03:11.602 --> 03:12.901
Yup.

03:12.936 --> 03:16.033
Why don't we just forget
about presents this year?

03:16.068 --> 03:17.400
Fine with me.

03:17.435 --> 03:20.033
I mean, after all, anniversaries
are about being together.

03:20.068 --> 03:21.267
Yeah, you're right.

03:21.302 --> 03:22.767
I'll come home tonight.
How's that?

03:24.200 --> 03:26.801
Yeah, I'll be here,
you'll be here,

03:26.836 --> 03:28.200
the TV will be here.

03:28.235 --> 03:30.901
Let's not make a big deal
about it this year, all right?

03:30.936 --> 03:32.968
Yeah. We don't need
a bunch of silly presents

03:33.003 --> 03:35.467
to show we love
each other.

03:35.502 --> 03:37.434
I know that I love you.

03:37.469 --> 03:38.934
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:38.969 --> 03:40.434
I said that I love you.

03:40.469 --> 03:43.334
I said yeah, yeah, yeah.
I got to get ready for work.

03:43.369 --> 03:45.868
Listen, Al, since you're not
gonna get me a present,

03:45.903 --> 03:47.534
do you think you could
take my car

03:47.569 --> 03:48.868
and have a radio installed?

03:48.903 --> 03:50.534
Peg, I don't have the time.

03:50.569 --> 03:52.868
Yeah, but I'm out all day long,
you know, running errands.

03:52.903 --> 03:54.667
What am I supposed
to listen to?

03:54.702 --> 03:56.167
Your own
beautiful voice.

03:56.202 --> 03:59.033
If God didn't want
other people to hear it,

03:59.068 --> 04:00.968
he wouldn't
have made it so shrill.

04:01.003 --> 04:02.901
I'm going
to take a shower.

04:02.936 --> 04:04.501
Yeah, I gotta do the laundry.

04:04.536 --> 04:06.734
When you do the laundry,
you use all the hot water.

04:06.769 --> 04:09.601
If God had wanted you
to have hot water,

04:09.636 --> 04:12.534
he wouldn't have
given me laundry.

04:12.569 --> 04:17.000
Dad, are you really not
gonna get Mom a present?

04:17.035 --> 04:21.434
Whoo, bad move.
No matter what she says,

04:21.469 --> 04:22.834
if you don't
get her a present,

04:22.869 --> 04:24.400
you're gonna break her heart.

04:24.435 --> 04:27.234
Yeah. Then she'll
take it out on us.

04:27.269 --> 04:30.501
Dad, even Meg's father got
her mom an anniversary present,

04:30.536 --> 04:32.367
and he shot at her.

04:34.000 --> 04:37.000
This is a secret.
And I mean a secret.

04:37.035 --> 04:39.501
I am getting
your mom a present-

04:39.536 --> 04:41.501
One of those
expensive watches

04:41.536 --> 04:43.934
she's always
harping about.

04:43.969 --> 04:46.968
Oh, Dad, that's great. She'll
love it, you're the greatest.

04:47.003 --> 04:48.968
Yeah, but listen, don't say
a word to your mother.

04:49.003 --> 04:50.767
Because I want this to be
a surprise, understand?

04:50.802 --> 04:51.968
Not a word.

04:52.003 --> 04:53.934
Right, Dad.

04:57.667 --> 04:59.467
Oh, Mom, guess what?

04:59.502 --> 05:01.033
Dad's getting
you a great watch.

05:01.068 --> 05:05.934
That is supposed
to be a surprise, butthead.

05:05.969 --> 05:07.367
It's one of those
expensive ones

05:07.402 --> 05:08.367
that you're always
harping about.

05:08.402 --> 05:10.067
Ohh...

05:10.102 --> 05:12.868
What a sweet man.

05:14.234 --> 05:18.267
Yeah, that sweet man
would get me a great gift,

05:18.302 --> 05:20.834
and I'll be sitting there like
a jerk with nothing for him.

05:20.869 --> 05:24.267
Well, I'm gonna go out
and get him something.

05:24.302 --> 05:26.634
What is it
he's really wanting?

05:26.669 --> 05:28.801
That blond
down the street.

05:30.834 --> 05:32.634
Did he tell you that?

05:32.669 --> 05:34.033
No, I just
assumed it

05:34.068 --> 05:35.434
by the way
he bites his fist

05:35.469 --> 05:38.834
whenever he
drives by her house.

05:38.869 --> 05:40.567
He's just kidding
when he does that.

05:40.602 --> 05:43.133
Excuse me. One second.

05:45.934 --> 05:47.534
Aah!

05:50.367 --> 05:52.000
Oh, I'm just kidding
when I do that.

05:52.035 --> 05:53.801
You kids go ahead
and get ready for school.

05:55.767 --> 05:57.100
Aah!

05:58.269 --> 06:01.601
Sorry, Al.
I had a huge load of laundry.

06:07.067 --> 06:09.033
Happy anniversary!
Happy anniversary!

06:09.068 --> 06:11.167
Ohh, how thoughtful!

06:11.202 --> 06:14.400
Look, we even put your name
on the label.

06:14.435 --> 06:15.767
Oh, that's too bad.

06:15.802 --> 06:18.000
It would have been nice gift
for us to give somebody,

06:18.035 --> 06:19.567
but thanks anyway.

06:21.567 --> 06:23.067
So...

06:23.102 --> 06:25.267
I guess you guys have
a big evening planned, huh?

06:25.302 --> 06:26.767
Oh, pretty much.

06:26.802 --> 06:29.100
I'll fix dinner.
We'll exchange presents.

06:29.135 --> 06:30.968
Then he'll watch
midget wrestling.

06:31.003 --> 06:33.000
Ooh. What time
does it come on?

06:33.035 --> 06:35.601
Steve! We hate wrestling.

06:35.636 --> 06:38.534
I know. I just
want to know

06:38.569 --> 06:42.167
how late midgets
got to stay up.

06:42.202 --> 06:43.167
Now, Peggy...

06:43.202 --> 06:46.067
This is a special
night for you.

06:46.102 --> 06:47.868
And you shouldn't
spend it cooking.

06:47.903 --> 06:50.367
Listen. I know
a great caterer.

06:50.402 --> 06:52.167
Let them do the work.

06:52.202 --> 06:53.367
A caterer?

06:53.402 --> 06:56.334
Yeah. We use them
for all our anniversaries.

06:56.369 --> 06:58.467
The first day we met.

06:58.502 --> 06:59.868
First day we kissed.

06:59.903 --> 07:02.467
The first day
we went out.

07:02.502 --> 07:04.734
The first day
we stayed in.

07:04.769 --> 07:06.767
The first day
you brought me flowers.

07:06.802 --> 07:08.367
The first day you
talked dirty to me.

07:08.402 --> 07:09.367
I love you, Steve.

07:09.402 --> 07:10.901
I love you too,
Marcie.

07:16.901 --> 07:18.267
Do they make veal?

07:20.734 --> 07:21.868
Here we are, sir.

07:21.903 --> 07:23.567
Oh, I think my wife
would like that.

07:23.602 --> 07:25.767
I think she will too,
it's a very nice frame and-

07:25.802 --> 07:28.734
I'm Al Bundy. I called
about that expensive watch.

07:28.769 --> 07:30.734
Ah, yes.

07:30.769 --> 07:32.267
Here you are, sir.

07:32.302 --> 07:33.767
It's my last one.

07:33.802 --> 07:35.767
Well, wrap it up, and...

07:35.802 --> 07:37.634
Leave the price tag on.

07:39.100 --> 07:40.601
Well, yes, sir.

07:40.636 --> 07:43.133
Will that be
cash or charge?

07:43.168 --> 07:44.934
Charge, and, uh...

07:44.969 --> 07:47.133
Don't get cute
with my carbons.

07:49.501 --> 07:52.367
Wait a second.
I was here first.

07:52.402 --> 07:54.234
Yeah. So were
the Indians.

07:55.534 --> 07:57.033
See, I'm in sales myself.

07:57.068 --> 07:59.033
I know how
these guys think.

07:59.068 --> 08:01.868
They see me,
they see a big commission.

08:01.903 --> 08:04.300
They see you,
they see me.

08:04.335 --> 08:06.467
Well, if you're in sales
you should know

08:06.502 --> 08:08.601
each customer counts
as much as the next.

08:08.636 --> 08:11.200
Yeah right, that's why he let
me butt right in front of you

08:11.235 --> 08:12.534
like you were never born.

08:12.569 --> 08:14.434
What's that?

08:14.469 --> 08:17.033
It's an anniversary
present for my wife.

08:17.068 --> 08:18.400
You gonna get that?

08:18.435 --> 08:19.400
Yeah.

08:19.435 --> 08:20.601
How many years
you been married?

08:20.636 --> 08:22.734
One.

08:22.769 --> 08:24.734
Well, see, that explains it.

08:24.769 --> 08:27.133
See, you're obviously new
to the married game.

08:27.168 --> 08:28.467
Let me help you out.

08:28.502 --> 08:31.901
See, the first thing I learned
on my 16-year tour of duty

08:31.936 --> 08:35.234
was that women
live for presents.

08:35.269 --> 08:37.534
Now you take the most ornery
woman in the world.

08:37.568 --> 08:39.801
We'll call her...Peggy.

08:41.767 --> 08:43.967
You bring
a crappy present home,

08:44.003 --> 08:47.667
like, uh...
that picture frame,

08:47.702 --> 08:50.534
and your life
will be a living hell.

08:50.569 --> 08:52.567
Well, my wife
and I agreed

08:52.602 --> 08:55.434
we wouldn't spend too much
on our anniversary.

08:55.469 --> 08:58.400
We decided we'd save our money
for more important things.

08:58.435 --> 09:01.601
There is no more important thing
than your anniversary.

09:01.636 --> 09:04.400
See, an anniversary
is something special.

09:04.435 --> 09:06.200
It's not like
other holidays

09:06.235 --> 09:08.501
when other people
are celebrating too.

09:08.536 --> 09:10.701
It's just between
the two of you.

09:10.736 --> 09:13.801
See, it's a day
when you can show

09:13.836 --> 09:16.501
how you feel the rest
of the year,

09:16.536 --> 09:19.167
but you don't,
because you're a man.

09:20.968 --> 09:22.634
That's beautiful.

09:22.669 --> 09:24.267
To know me is to love me.

09:26.133 --> 09:29.133
Here comes
how I feel right now.

09:29.168 --> 09:31.133
Sir, your card's
been rejected.

09:31.168 --> 09:32.300
Why?

09:32.335 --> 09:35.033
I don't care. Next.

09:35.068 --> 09:36.534
Wait a second.
It's my anniversary.

09:36.569 --> 09:37.968
Happy anniversary.

09:38.003 --> 09:39.033
Next.

09:39.068 --> 09:40.400
I'll take the watch.

09:45.801 --> 09:48.901
Wow, I wish I could make
stuff like that.

09:48.936 --> 09:51.968
Maybe you can.
Would like to be a chef?

09:52.003 --> 09:54.467
No, I'd rather
be a man.

